# Non-secret config (recipients, healthcheck URLs, thresholds) lives in a
# single source of truth: state/angelus.env. The cron entry below sources it
# so belfry and the daemon read the same values and can't diverge (B16).
# Copy state/angelus.env.example to state/angelus.env and fill it in.
#
# PATH must include wherever your notification command is installed. Set it
# either here in the crontab or inside state/angelus.env. Precedence: a var
# set in the crontab BELOW the sourcing wins; the file fills in the rest.
# PATH=/home/you/.local/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
#
# These now live in state/angelus.env rather than here:
#   ANGELUS_BELFRY_SUCCESS_URL=https://hc-ping.com/<angelus-belfry-ping-uuid>
#   ANGELUS_BELFRY_DOWN_URL=https://hc-ping.com/<angelus-daemon-down-uuid>
#
# Belfry's notify() sends to ANGELUS_EMAIL_TO via the command in
# ANGELUS_BELFRY_NOTIFY_COMMAND (defaults to bare 'patbot-email' on PATH).
# Both live in state/angelus.env. If ANGELUS_EMAIL_TO is unset notify()
# silently no-ops and the only escalation channel left is the DOWN_URL
# healthcheck ping. Set ANGELUS_BELFRY_NOTIFY_COMMAND to an absolute path
# because cron PATH is usually stripped.
#
# ANGELUS_BELFRY_WEDGE_THRESHOLD_SEC (optional) and
# ANGELUS_BELFRY_FAILCHECK_PATH (optional) also live in state/angelus.env --
# see state/angelus.env.example for all the knobs and their defaults.
#
# The entry sources state/angelus.env (set -a exports each var) before
# running belfry. belfry.py also loads the same file in code, so the source
# step here is mainly to put PATH in place for `/usr/bin/env python`.
# The leading '[ -f ... ]' keeps a missing file from aborting the tick.

*/5 * * * * cd /path/to/angelus && { set -a; [ -f state/angelus.env ] && . state/angelus.env; set +a; }; /usr/bin/env python belfry/belfry.py >> state/belfry.log 2>&1
